Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.22,0:00:17.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I mustn't go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.18,0:00:22.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We would run and run, but to where?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.60,0:00:26.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no place that is safe for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.15,0:00:29.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.57,0:00:33.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am glad that you came for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.16,0:00:39.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But there is no path ahead \Nof us to travel down yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.20,0:00:45.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. This is not a time \Nto attempt to do too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.31,0:01:02.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is it because of the snow?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.70,0:01:15.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lieselotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.59,0:01:18.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have no one to blame but yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.33,0:01:22.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was you who betrayed us Magiuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.33,0:01:24.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I did not betray you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.33,0:01:29.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply wanted to do the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.10,0:03:07.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Module 77 has been targeted for attack?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.18,0:03:11.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. A space-model Phantom \Nis en route to the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.81,0:03:13.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But the Moon is neutral!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.69,0:03:16.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but these guys attacked \NJIOR, and we were neutral, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.07,0:03:19.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back to the Moon! Module \N77 is completely defenseless!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.99,0:03:22.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't seen what the \Nsituation is in JIOR yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.13,0:03:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or met up with Ms. Rukino, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.87,0:03:26.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if we don't have a place to go home \Nto, all this will have been for nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.75,0:03:29.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know, but we...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.13,0:03:34.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,L-elf! What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.42,0:03:39.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.59,0:03:44.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The supplies we received from the \NRoyalists also contained intel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.60,0:03:50.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is that, a rocket?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.06,0:03:53.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, what an antique.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.00,0:03:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a multi-stage design \Nfrom over 100 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.11,0:03:57.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You want us to use this museum piece?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.78,0:04:00.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's exactly why the Dorssian \Nmilitary security will be light.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.78,0:04:02.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.62,0:04:06.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.66,0:04:08.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those are JIORan names.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.79,0:04:10.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,These are JIORans who \Nwere taken by force
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.92,0:04:12.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the town where we're headed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.33,0:04:15.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we rescue them, we can ascertain \Nthe situation inside JIOR.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.63,0:04:17.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which will essentially \Nlet us complete the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.54,0:04:19.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,objective of the force recon mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.84,0:04:21.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But still...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.05,0:04:23.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That all depends on what sort of \Npeople were taken into custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.84,0:04:27.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the reason, we \Ngotta help these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.26,0:04:28.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.39,0:04:30.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My dad's name is on here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.93,0:04:31.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.81,0:04:32.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.79,0:04:34.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,SOUICHI TOKISHIMA
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.77,0:04:36.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are there more? Do you \Nrecognize any others?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.49,0:04:38.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- Is my old man on there? \N- What about my mom?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.44,0:04:39.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is my grandpa on there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.57,0:04:40.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the whole list?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.69,0:04:42.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I know this name!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.40,0:04:44.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not there! It's not there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.36,0:04:46.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible that the families of \Neveryone back at the Moon are on here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.99,0:04:48.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.20,0:04:49.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's look for them!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.63,0:05:00.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for making you \Ngo to all this trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.01,0:05:01.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do not mention it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.42,0:05:04.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However little it may \Nbe, locked away as I am,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.10,0:05:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will do anything in \Nmy power to assist you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.89,0:05:12.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What sort of authorization \Nis it this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.26,0:05:15.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it to help an ideological criminal?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.52,0:05:18.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or someone with ties to \Nthe royal family, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.27,0:05:20.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's for JIORans.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.04,0:05:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The students who have \Ncome down to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.57,0:05:25.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you don't mean—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.78,0:05:27.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will this be a problem for you, Miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.45,0:05:31.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, none at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.75,0:05:34.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Michael...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.98,0:05:53.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The thing is, H-neun was \Nselling military intel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.73,0:06:00.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It had to be done, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.98,0:06:04.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Death to traitors" and \Nall that, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.38,0:06:22.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I had known he was a traitor,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.98,0:06:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would have fought him myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.39,0:06:38.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's old-fashioned, but \Nthis city is rather lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.85,0:06:40.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The old capital, Dorssiana.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.60,0:06:43.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was the capital of the Kingdom \Nof Dorssia for a thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.86,0:06:45.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A thousand?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.07,0:06:47.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that shows how much support the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.10,0:06:48.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,royal family had from the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.99,0:06:51.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But they say most of the \Nroyals were locked up
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.91,0:06:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the coup 10 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.97,0:06:55.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Red Thursday...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.03,0:06:58.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That marked the day that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.01,0:07:01.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dorssia began expanding across \Nthe globe as a military state.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.63,0:07:05.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This district has been turned \Ninto a total ghost town,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.19,0:07:07.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so I guess that make the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.79,0:07:09.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Royalists feel free to \Noperate with impunity here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.60,0:07:15.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.66,0:07:41.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Switch successful...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.50,0:07:42.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This will let you see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.84,0:07:46.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your father, I mean. I'm jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.17,0:07:48.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.72,0:07:50.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't feel guilty on our account.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.17,0:07:52.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.05,0:07:54.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.64,0:07:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't seen my father all that often.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.31,0:08:03.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He was busy with work all the \Ntime. He was hardly ever at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.23,0:08:05.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He was a researcher at a \Npharmaceutical company.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.14,0:08:07.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A total genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.15,0:08:14.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I never knew \Nwhat to say to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.49,0:08:17.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I was afraid that \Nhe'd be disappointed in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.41,0:08:20.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But after all this,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.67,0:08:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll be able to \Nactually talk with him now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.23,0:08:46.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this looks good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.79,0:08:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's give it a try with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.40,0:08:49.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.78,0:08:52.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? What's that, Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.32,0:08:55.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.78,0:08:59.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Haruto Tokishima. He's my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.62,0:09:01.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your son?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.75,0:09:02.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.33,0:09:06.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Haruto here is my pride and joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.18,0:09:17.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.52,0:09:22.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare for battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.41,0:09:38.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Backbone line infiltration successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.08,0:09:45.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Address: Kaiserburg, \Ndistrict 672, D-5421.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.42,0:09:48.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The museum is now closed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.71,0:09:52.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We ask that all visitors please \Nvacate the building immediately.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.01,0:09:55.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Museum. Main system.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.84,0:09:59.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Down a level. Guard room. Camera...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.28,0:10:16.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's the signal from Akira!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.36,0:10:19.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're leaving as soon as Haruto \Nand the others get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.44,0:10:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.10,0:10:52.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea you were a \Nfellow Royalist, Kriemhild.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.86,0:10:54.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your night vision is as \Nsharp as ever, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.07,0:10:55.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You know her?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.99,0:10:57.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She's a former superior officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.78,0:11:00.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The JIORans taken into custody \Nare being held underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.53,0:11:02.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can only take you as \Nfar as the duct entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.24,0:11:04.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Finish up inside of two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.04,0:11:06.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.73,0:11:09.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But aren't you going to \Nask why I turned traitor?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.13,0:11:12.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't led a life that's \Nbeen so happy-go-lucky
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.45,0:11:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that I believe answers to my questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.34,0:11:16.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My men will show you to the duct.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.26,0:11:19.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. We should be able to \Nbegin the operation immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.81,0:11:29.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just out of curiosity, is anyone \Nin your group named Michael?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.56,0:11:32.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, there isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.65,0:11:35.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Michael? That isn't a JIORan name.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.65,0:11:37.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Forget I asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.90,0:11:39.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.82,0:11:44.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I joined the Karlstein Agency, \Nmy name was taken from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.29,0:11:51.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The name I was given was the \Nidentification code "L, number 11."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.03,0:11:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,L-elf.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.79,0:11:54.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it... It's you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.21,0:11:58.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,On the door to this hangar, there \Nwas a crest with seven dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.30,0:12:00.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That means it's reserved \Nfor royal family use.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.38,0:12:02.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,L-elf, don't stick your nose \Nwhere it doesn't belong.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.47,0:12:07.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To use it, the signature of someone in \Nthe royal line of succession is needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.60,0:12:10.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There are currently 63 people \Nin line for the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.69,0:12:14.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of those, 56 are confirmed to be \Nresiding outside of Dorssiana.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.86,0:12:18.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, there are 7 who \Ncould have provided a signature.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.65,0:12:21.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And of those 7, the only one \Nwho knows my old name...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.91,0:12:24.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...is her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.57,0:12:26.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By "her" you mean... the \Ngirl in the picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.08,0:12:28.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you to drop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.91,0:12:30.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My pre-Karlstein name.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.71,0:12:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The seven dragons on the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.94,0:12:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A royal in line for the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.42,0:12:37.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The conclusion I'm led to is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.88,0:12:43.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.93,0:12:45.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,L-elf! Stop where you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.43,0:12:51.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant Commander! What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.89,0:12:54.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is he doing? \NWhat about the plan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.35,0:12:56.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not safe to be away from L-elf.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.26,0:12:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go after him, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.15,0:12:57.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.57,0:12:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's proceed according to plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.07,0:13:00.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tokishima?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.94,0:13:02.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You want to do this without L-elf?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.03,0:13:04.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to fight our own battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.41,0:13:09.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just like we want to see our \Nfamilies and keep our friends safe,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.91,0:13:12.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,he has his own reasons to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.51,0:13:22.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're a long way down...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.38,0:13:25.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,According to her description, \Nwe're 100 meters underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.22,0:13:29.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that shows how \Nimportant the prisoners are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.22,0:13:31.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, they brought them \Nhere all the way from JIOR.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.64,0:13:32.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.84,0:13:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dad is a simple office worker.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.72,0:14:08.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ship registry number, DS-HUW40768S254.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.35,0:14:12.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought, this is the ship \Nthat L-elf and his people stole.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.48,0:14:14.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We won't be facing only students.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.35,0:14:17.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's a chance that \NL-elf is here, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.81,0:14:21.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be very cautious \Nwhen it comes to L-elf, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.52,0:14:24.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's because he's an opponent \Nyou must be cautious with.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.33,0:14:25.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.91,0:14:28.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.48,0:14:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see to the hangar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.03,0:14:31.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Blitzendegen!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.29,0:14:42.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is this where we were supposed \Nto meet our contact?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.59,0:14:44.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.01,0:14:45.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's cold, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.68,0:14:49.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, are you our...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.05,0:14:51.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the kids from JIOR?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.31,0:14:56.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. We're here \Nto break you all out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.48,0:14:58.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Help has arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.52,0:14:59.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just like she said!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.94,0:15:02.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She was telling the \Ntruth! We can go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.32,0:15:04.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! We have to bring our data!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.28,0:15:07.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, is there a man here \Nby the name of Souichi Tokishima?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.98,0:15:09.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Tokishima?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.07,0:15:13.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Souichi Tokishima is my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.08,0:15:18.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, he is? Then you're the...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.16,0:15:20.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're the boy who's fighting \Nthe whole world, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.88,0:15:23.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is this fate? Or karma?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.77,0:15:24.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shut it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.67,0:15:25.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Karma?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.71,0:15:28.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tokishima. There's something \NI haven't told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.49,0:15:30.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Haruto!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.65,0:15:33.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Haruto, I'm so glad to see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.30,0:15:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dorssia sure is cold, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.09,0:15:36.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.31,0:15:38.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How are you, my boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.20,0:15:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No health problems, I hope?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.47,0:15:43.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it out, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.60,0:15:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have a look at you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.98,0:15:46.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine! I'm not a child!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.44,0:15:49.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That tickles, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.49,0:15:51.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.12,0:15:55.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time, Dad. \NWhat's it been, three years?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.83,0:15:57.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose it has!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.78,0:16:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I haven't forgotten \Nyou for a single moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.88,0:16:05.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've had a photo of you on \Nmy desk this whole time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.59,0:16:07.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? A picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.17,0:16:11.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I look at it all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.54,0:16:13.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you're my pride and joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.80,0:16:16.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,See? This is the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.18,0:16:22.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it beautiful, Haruto? This is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.35,0:16:24.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What... is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.11,0:16:29.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is your gene map! My masterpiece!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.53,0:16:33.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't the alignment of this \NN sequence a thing of beauty?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.95,0:16:35.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.62,0:16:39.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tokishima is the scientist \Nin charge of the VVV Project.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.96,0:16:44.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? But Dad, You said you worked \Nfor a pharmaceutical company.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.88,0:16:47.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that was a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.25,0:16:50.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The VVV Project was the highest \Nof state secrets, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.88,0:16:52.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was camouflage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.76,0:16:56.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then... Then you were \Nmaking weapons, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.56,0:16:57.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tools for killing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.97,0:16:59.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Weapons"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.23,0:17:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Valvraves are nothing \Nso crude as that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.64,0:17:04.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our sponsor was the military,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.68,0:17:07.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we slapped armor and weapons \Nonto them, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.40,0:17:13.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The real goal of the Valvraves \Nis to create a new form of life!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.78,0:17:19.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! You have surpassed humanity!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.33,0:17:22.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's the birth of Homo sapiens novus,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.02,0:17:26.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which will rule all humanity on \NEarth! No, the entire universe!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.30,0:17:35.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Haruto, you and the others \Nare the chosen few,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.78,0:17:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,modified for the VVV Project!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.22,0:17:39.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Modified?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.11,0:17:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, "project"?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.02,0:17:45.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The project to develop the \NValvraves and their pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.69,0:17:49.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You were created through \Ngenetic and Rune manipulation
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.93,0:17:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to make you compatible \Nwith the Valvraves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.53,0:17:54.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What gave you the right \Nto do that to us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.57,0:17:55.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, we had permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.20,0:17:58.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I sure don't remember giving \Nanybody my permission!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.53,0:18:00.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Silly boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.04,0:18:02.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This was before you were born!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.77,0:18:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was your parents who gave \Nme permission, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.83,0:18:07.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I did not! I was tricked!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.29,0:18:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did it out of idealism!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.63,0:18:12.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it doesn't changed the fact that \Nyou were willing participants!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.00,0:18:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you can't go public!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.42,0:18:17.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the children of the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.27,0:18:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,VVV Project personnel are both \Ntest subjects and leverage!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.39,0:18:23.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Two birds with one stone, am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.73,0:18:30.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I have to meet up with the others and \Ntell them what the enemy's up to!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.49,0:18:39.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's deserted? What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.28,0:18:41.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,L-elf...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.83,0:18:44.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've located the transport \Nthat was stolen by L-elf
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.92,0:18:47.31,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,and his people in the forest \N30km east of Dorssiana.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.96,0:18:50.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}However, no one is on board.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.92,0:18:53.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If they've deserted the \Ntransport, that means
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.21,0:18:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they've set their sights on \Nanother means of transportation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.88,0:19:00.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To carry the Valvraves, \Nthey'd need something big.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.93,0:19:04.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The only civilian craft \Nbig enough would be...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.64,0:19:08.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...at this base!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.10,0:19:10.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.55,0:19:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your line of reasoning \Nis not bad at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.48,0:19:16.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Q-vier, now departing for \Nbattle! Blitzendegen!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.82,0:19:19.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't given you any such order yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.91,0:19:24.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then. Isn't there \Nanother possibility?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.79,0:19:28.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The possibility that they are \Nreceiving Royalist assistance...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.71,0:19:32.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...is rather high, wouldn't you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.18,0:19:50.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This should bring something capable \Nof breaching the tower wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.77,0:19:52.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,L-elf's been spotted?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.31,0:19:54.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, Haruto.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.36,0:19:56.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're a special being who has received
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.76,0:19:58.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the blessings of the power of science!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.61,0:20:01.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not even the Dorssian \Nmilitary will turn you away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.03,0:20:04.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Blessing? What you gave us is a curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.45,0:20:06.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We lose our memories! Our minds!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.85,0:20:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We live by devouring other people!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.41,0:20:12.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Homo sapiens novus stands at \Nthe top of the food chain.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.17,0:20:16.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What you describe is as natural \Nas a human eating a fish or pig!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.21,0:20:17.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.17,0:20:19.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hold your head high, Haruto!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.12,0:20:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've become the ultimate lifeform!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.84,0:20:26.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As the person who created you, \Nfrom a scientific standpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.43,0:20:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,does that make me God?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.81,0:20:35.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tokishima! Please \Nstop antagonizing him!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.46,0:20:41.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Haruto?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.74,0:20:43.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Ultimate lifeform," my ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.23,0:20:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tons of people have died because of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.12,0:20:50.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aina and Marie and lots of JIORans!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.24,0:20:53.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about a thing, Haruto.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.17,0:20:56.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A Homo sapien novus like \Nyou won't die so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.42,0:20:58.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Haruto...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.76,0:21:01.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.76,0:21:03.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.56,0:21:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I made up my mind a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.89,0:21:08.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.47,0:21:11.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to destroy the Valvraves.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.14,0:21:14.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To make sure this curse \Ndoesn't spread any further,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.64,0:21:15.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make sure nothing's left!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.73,0:21:21.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do that, Haruto!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.32,0:21:24.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the living \Nembodiment of my dreams!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.49,0:21:25.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to end humanity's future?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.82,0:21:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To hold back the clock \Nof human evolution?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.49,0:21:29.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stop this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.33,0:21:30.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.95,0:21:32.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.73,0:21:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything has worked out so well!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.08,0:21:37.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.37,0:21:40.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.07,0:22:09.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Why did you...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.66,0:22:14.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't like three years \Nago. I've created a path.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.17,0:22:17.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I now have a country to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.42,0:22:20.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lieselotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.67,0:22:24.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Michael...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.18,0:22:33.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to abduct you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.32,0:24:18.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, episode 19.\N "Sadness is Like the Falling Snow."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.58,0:24:21.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Valvrave the Liberator...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.52,0:24:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.52,0:24:24.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The system that will expose \Nthe truth of the world.